<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7543> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7543" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 74, juror in the trial of Oppianicus (Cic. Cluent. 107). Münzer suggested that these two were really one person; so, too, Wiseman, CQ 14, 1964, 124, both agreeing that L. is the correct praenomen. See Shackleton Bailey, Studies 56.[151]" .
